verses.roman:
pāche pāche cali' yāya āra bhakta-gaṇa
utkaṇṭhāte gelā saba jagannātha-bhavana

synonyms: pāche pāche-following; cali' yāya-walk; āra-other; bhakta-gaṇa-devotees; utkaṇṭhāte-in great anxiety; gelā-they went; saba-all; jagannātha-bhavana-in the temple of Lord Jagannātha.
translation: With great anxiety all the other devotees followed them into the temple of Lord Jagannātha.
